	     Cape Town – A 25-year-old man was shot dead and three others were wounded during a shooting in Scottsdene, Kraaifontein, on Thursday, Western Cape police said. Captain Nopaya Madyibi said the three men, aged 17, had been taken to hospital.  The shooting happened around 10:00 on Thursday morning.  Madyibi said circumstances surrounding the incident were still unknown.  Police were investigating murder and three attempted murder cases.  No arrests had been made.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  